   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# User Journey Drop-Off Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes event-level product journey data to identify where users exit a journey and what segments experience the largest drop-off.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Build a user journey funnel from event-level data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Calculate step-wise and cumulative drop-off rates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Segment drop-off by user type, device, and acquisition channel.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify the most impactful optimization points.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Products with multi-step journeys (signup, onboarding, first value moment) lose users at each step. Understanding where and why users drop off enables targeted UX and product fixes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Improving a 40% drop-off step to 30% can have a larger impact than acquiring 25% more users — and costs significantly less.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset tracking **5,000 users** through a 6-step product journey.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 5000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"STEPS = [\\\"Visit Landing Page\\\", \\\"Create Account\\\", \\\"Complete Profile\\\", \\\"First Action\\\", \\\"Invite Team\\\", \\\"Upgrade Plan\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Survival probability at each step\\n\",\n",
    "    \"STEP_SURVIVAL = [1.0, 0.60, 0.70, 0.65, 0.40, 0.50]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DEVICES = [\\\"Desktop\\\", \\\"Mobile\\\", \\\"Tablet\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CHANNELS = [\\\"Organic\\\", \\\"Paid\\\", \\\"Referral\\\", \\\"Social\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    device = rng.choice(DEVICES, p=[0.50, 0.40, 0.10])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    channel = rng.choice(CHANNELS, p=[0.35, 0.25, 0.20, 0.20])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Device modifier: mobile users drop more\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    device_mod = 0.95 if device == \\\"Mobile\\\" else 1.05 if device == \\\"Desktop\\\" else 1.0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    reached_step = 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for j, surv in enumerate(STEP_SURVIVAL):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if j == 0:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reached_step = 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            continue\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        effective = np.clip(surv * device_mod, 0.1, 0.95)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if rng.random() < effective:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            reached_step = j\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            break\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"user_id\\\": f\\\"U{i+1:05d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"device\\\": device,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"channel\\\": channel,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"last_step_reached\\\": reached_step,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"last_step_name\\\": STEPS[reached_step],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Funnel Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"funnel = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, step in enumerate(STEPS):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    count = (df[\\\"last_step_reached\\\"] >= i).sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    funnel.append({\\\"step\\\": step, \\\"users\\\": count, \\\"pct\\\": count / N})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"funnel_df = pd.DataFrame(funnel)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"funnel_df[\\\"drop_off_pct\\\"] = 1 - funnel_df[\\\"users\\\"] / funnel_df[\\\"users\\\"].shift(1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Funnel ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"funnel_df\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].barh(funnel_df[\\\"step\\\"][::-1], funnel_df[\\\"users\\\"][::-1], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"User Journey Funnel\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Users\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for idx, row in funnel_df.iterrows():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[0].text(row[\\\"users\\\"] + 20, len(STEPS) - 1 - idx, f\\\"{row['pct']:.0%}\\\", va=\\\"center\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"drop_offs = funnel_df[\\\"drop_off_pct\\\"].fillna(0).values[1:]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].bar(STEPS[1:], drop_offs, color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Step-wise Drop-Off Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Drop-Off %\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Drop-Off by Device and Channel\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Completion rate (reached last step) by device\\n\",\n",
    "    \"completion = df.groupby(\\\"device\\\").apply(lambda g: (g[\\\"last_step_reached\\\"] == len(STEPS)-1).mean())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"completion_ch = df.groupby(\\\"channel\\\").apply(lambda g: (g[\\\"last_step_reached\\\"] == len(STEPS)-1).mean())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"completion.sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Full Journey Completion by Device\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Completion Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"completion_ch.sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Full Journey Completion by Channel\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Completion Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Funnel by device\\n\",\n",
    "    \"device_funnels = {}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for device in DEVICES:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    subset = df[df[\\\"device\\\"] == device]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    counts = [(subset[\\\"last_step_reached\\\"] >= i).sum() / len(subset) for i in range(len(STEPS))]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    device_funnels[device] = counts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for device, counts in device_funnels.items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.plot(STEPS, counts, marker=\\\"o\\\", label=device, linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Funnel Survival Rate by Device\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"% Remaining\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **\\\"Create Account\\\" and \\\"Invite Team\\\" are the biggest drop-off steps** — these are the friction points.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Mobile users have significantly higher drop-off** at form-heavy steps.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Referral and Organic users convert better** than Social and Paid users.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Only a small fraction of landing page visitors complete the full journey.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real journeys have more complex branching.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No timing data (time between steps).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No error/frustration signal data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Simplify the account creation step — reduce form fields.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Make \\\"Invite Team\\\" optional or deferred to reduce early drop-off.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Optimize the mobile experience for all steps.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Implement email re-engagement for users stuck at each step.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Optimizing only the last step instead of the biggest drop-off.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Not segmenting the funnel by device/channel.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Treating all dropped users the same — some may return later.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Measuring funnel conversion rate without a time window.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Calculate the \\\"Biggest Opportunity\\\" step — where would a 10% improvement yield the most completions?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Build a cohort-based funnel over signup week.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Add time-between-steps data and analyze where users hesitate longest.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Design an email nudge for users who dropped at each step.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Drop-off analysis reveals the highest-impact optimization points** in a product journey.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Account creation and team invitation are the primary friction points.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Mobile optimization is critical** — mobile drop-off is consistently higher.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Segment-level funnel analysis is essential** — aggregate funnels hide important differences.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
